    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_vm.01965_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Anderton, near Chorley</name>
                    <name type="place">Lancashire, England</name>
                    <date when="1891-12-16">16 Dec. 1891</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Walt,</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>I haven't time now to write a proper letter, but I cannot let the mail go without sending a 
                line or two to express my constant thoughts of you,
               &#38; my loving good wishes.</p>
            <p>I called at Dr J's<ptr target="n4102"/> last night, &#38; he lent me Lynch's 
                "Modern Authors"<ptr target="loc.04827_n1"/> which he 
                had just received. Greenhalgh<ptr target="loc.02465_n5"/>
               called while I
                <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc_vm.01968_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
                <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc_vm.01966_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
                was there. All well</p>
            <p>Hoping to hear a better account of you</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>Yours affectionately</salute>
                <signed><hi rend="underline">J.W. Wallace</hi></signed>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="loc_vm.01967_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
        </body>
    </text> 
